While their Absa Premiership title challengers have used big budgets to buy proven talent at this level or pay large wages for free agents Pirates have rather scratched around in search of the next big thing.We look back at their major signings of the last three transfer windows not including this current January one and assesses their accuracy in the market and whether those players they have brought in have proven a hit a miss or whether the jury is still out.2016/17 SEASON Justice Chabalala:Chabalala looked a raw talent but a promising one in the first half of the season but was then shipped out after six months to Chippa United so we can only assume he did not fit into the team dynamics.Verdict: Miss&nbsp;